The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Salma Bibi, a 32-year-old homemaker, was allegedly burnt to death in her Cossipore Road home on Tuesday night. Salmas mother lodged a complaint accusing Salmas husband Sheikh Shahid of torturing and murdering her daughter. Salmas five-year-old daughter told police that she had seen her father pour kerosene on her mother and set her on fire. Shahid was arrested on Wednesday.     The state election commission on Wednesday published the list of reserved wards for the Bidhannagar Municipality polls. The wards were re-aligned last month. Ward 1 has been reserved for scheduled caste women, wards 2, 5, 8, 11, 14, 17, 20 and 25 for women and wards 22 and 23 for scheduled caste and scheduled tribe candidates.    Lawyers of Alipore Bar Association boycotted court proceedings on Tuesday demanding resolution of a dispute between a lawyer and a court employee on February 25. With only the case of alleged Maoist leader Venkateshwar Reddy being heard on Wednesday, litigants faced inconvenience. A Bar Association spokesman said the boycott would continue on Thursday.    A SIM card was found on Mohammad Shamim, a middle-aged prisoner in Alipore Central jail, on Wednesday evening. Cops suspect some visitors gave the card to Shamim in a food packet on Wednesday afternoon.     A trailer rammed in to a taxi late on Wednesday on the western slope of No. 4 bridge near Park Circus. No one were injured but the mishap caused a massive traffic snarl at the crossing as both vehicles broke down and blocked the road. Police later removed the vehicles.     A 43.5 kg-tumour was removed from the ovary of a 58-year-old resident of East Midnapore on Wednesday in a three-hour surgery at SSKM Hospital. The operation was conducted by D.N. Sil and Sambhunath Banerjee in the presence of the head of the gynaecology and obstetrics department, T.K. Ghosh.                                                                                                                                                  
